Kan Signals He’ll Step Down After Japan Crisis

-- B y   S a c h i k o   S a k a m a k i
-- 
2011-06-02T03:23:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/kan-signals-he-ll-step-down-after-japan-crisis-over.html
Japan ’s Prime Minister  Naoto Kan  said
he’s willing to step down and pass responsibility to a younger
generation once his work is accomplished. Kan, who spoke today
in a meeting of the  Democratic Party  of Japan, has said he wants
to finish his work helping the country recover from the March 11
earthquake, tsunami and nuclear disaster.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sachiko Sakamaki in Tokyo at 
 ssakamaki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
